@harshach, returning all topic names to the client even if the client doesn't have `Describe Topic` permission is an information leak and we definitely need to fix that (as per KAFKA-3396). This can lead to unexpected behaviour in this case (as I said in the JIRA for this PR), but I don't see a way around that.

~~In any case, the suggested change still makes sense once KAFKA-3396 lands as even if we don't return the unauthorized topics that the user doesn't have `Describe Topic` permission for, there is still the case where the user has `Describe Topic` permission, but no `Create` permission for the auto-topic creation case.~~ Edit: Auto-creation of topics doesn't happen for pattern subscriptions, so what I had said about that doesn't make sense. Given that, it's less clear if this change makes sense for trunk. Maybe for `0.10.0` though.

cc @hachikuji

I think this change makes sense to do. 

@granthenke raised a security concern in https://github.com/apache/kafka/pull/557#issuecomment-185442232, IMO the tradeoff is worth it. It seems better to respect `$PATH` than hardcode the path to bash (we'd be hardcoding `/usr/bin/env` but that seems pretty standard for portable scripts?).

@aloiscochard seems there have been a more scripts added to `bin/` since you created the PR
